{"word":"ἔνδοξος","slug":"ἔνδοξος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἔνδοξος</b></el> adj (e)n-doc os_on) <p/><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:δόξα'><el>δόξα</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>held in esteem</i> or <i>honour, of high repute</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of things, <i>notable</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschines'>Aeschin.</a></b>: —<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-ξως</el>, hence <a href='S:Superlative'>Sup.</a>, <el>ἐνδοξότατα</el> <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}